episodes.title: Welcome to Miami
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q take their talents to Miami, pulling all new pranks on the beach. The guys zip around in scooters controlled by the other Jokers, and the loser will come face-to-face with an alligator.

episodes.title: Below the Belt
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q teach fencing, and one Joker is especially "en garde" when forced to face an Olympian. The guys trim away their dignity as hairstylists, and the punished Joker melts down during a presentation on climate change.

episodes.title: Uncool and the Gang
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q host a team building seminar that's NOT safe for work, and then, they pose as caricature artists on a boardwalk. Plus, the wheels come off for tonight's loser as he faces a confused and unamused biker gang.

episodes.title: Wrong Playwright
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr, and Q hit the supermarket to mess with shoppers in an epic game of Hide-and-Sneak, the guys draw straws at a BBQ joint, and tonight's loser gets a bad case of stage fright while giving the performance of his life.

episodes.title: Elevating the Game
episodes.plot: The guys work the register at a burger restaurant before taking their fun to a department store. Later, the loser faces their fears in a terrifying elevator ride.

episodes.title: The Blunder Years
episodes.plot: The guys try to humiliate each other at a convenience store before visiting a wedding expo. Later, the loser must face his childhood crush, Danica McKellar (from The Wonder Years) wearing nothing but a skimpy Speedo.

episodes.title: Deal with the Devils
episodes.plot: The guys head to a library to make some noise. Later, they search for missing people at the mall and the loser has to hit the ice with the New Jersey Devils.

episodes.title: Damned If You Do
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q take to the ice for a very slippery game. Then they head to the park to get support for some ridiculous causes, and the loser is forced to relive the sins of his past before a captive, critical audience.

episodes.title: The Dream Crusher
episodes.plot: The guys try to kiss unsuspecting strangers (until a special guest crashes the party), they focus-group their absurd life stories as potential movies, and the big loser gets a room full of enemies while judging a kids' talent show.

episodes.title: Joke & Dagger
episodes.plot: The guys crash a gallery opening where their antics aren't appreciated, they pass bizarre judgment on unsuspecting grocery shoppers, and the loser takes a spin on a terrifying wheel, where one wrong move could have deadly consequences.

episodes.title: Pseudo-Sumo
episodes.plot: The guys freeze out skaters at an ice rink's rental counter and head to the mall where they have the audacity to ask strangers to mind their manners. Then, the loser is down for the count after donning a diaper for a sumo-sized punishment.

episodes.title: Car Sick
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q freak out a focus group by reading ridiculous answers and then participate in a thrilling toilet paper shootout in their favorite market. Plus, the loser's fancy dinner party turns into the messiest ride of his life.

episodes.title: Cruisin' for a Bruisin'
episodes.plot: The guys hit the seas for a special cruise episode! They turn the pool deck into a playground, give misinformation while posing as entertainment directors, and two Jokers get a double dose of torture in a two part punishment!

episodes.title: Bathroom Break
episodes.plot: The guys get sassy while posing as auto parts salesmen, then head to the mall where they try to reel in unsuspecting shoppers. And the big loser is stuck in a horrible mess after being locked inside a rigged bathroom of horrors.

episodes.title: Kill the Centaur
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q get ballsy while posing as salesmen, and then try to outdo each other as they invade the personal space of confused strangers. And loser is up against the ropes, playing dress-up for an unruly arena.

episodes.title: Captain Fatbelly
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q lend an unhelpful hand while working at a high-tech store, then play detectives at the mall in search of perps on the loose. And the loser gets the shakes while soaring high above the city.

episodes.title: Sneaking Number Twos, Going Number One
episodes.plot: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr play a game of "Put-Pocket" at a grocery store, then get jumpy at the park after taking over each other's cell phones. And the big loser learns that when you gotta go...you gotta go.

episodes.title: Blind Justice
episodes.plot: The guys get a little punchy while giving boxing lessons, then head to the mall to share the gift of music with strangers. And when the loser delivers the right speech to the wrong audience, he's the one who gets scared straight.

episodes.title: Tied and Feathered
episodes.plot: The guys teach a crash course in sorry behavior, ask strangers to settle bizarre debates, and spread surprisingly good news at the mall. Plus, the loser has his hands tied when a day at the park turns into a frightful mess.

episodes.title: Smushed
episodes.plot: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr give a security presentation that's anything but safe, then hold hands with strangers in the park. And the big loser quickly becomes an unwanted guest while clowning around at a kid's birthday party.

episodes.title: Anatomy of a Challenge
episodes.plot: Joe, Murr, Q, and Sal break down how to succeed in each challenge and how to make each other trip up and lose.

episodes.title: Unseen Scenes
episodes.plot: Check out deleted scenes from Impractical Jokers challenges.

episodes.title: Fan-tastic Countdown
episodes.plot: The Jokers count down the most memorable moments of the show, as requested by their fans.

episodes.title: Live Punishment Special
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr will take on their most challenging dare yet: an epic high-wire walk five stories in the air above New York City during the show's first ever live punishment extravaganza. With multiple cameras positioned to capture every moment and New York City's South Street Seaport as the backdrop, the quartet known for challenging one another to do the most outrageous dares in public will attempt to outdo each other to see who can walk the farthest distance. In the can't-miss Impractical Jokers Live Punishment Special will reveal which Joker will be the first...

episodes.title: The Big Uneasy
episodes.plot: The guys take over New Orleans, as they steal sips from strangers' drinks at a famous bar, spin the Wheel of Voo-Doom on Bourbon Street, and crash some horse and buggy rides. Then, tonight's loser turns into a legendary swamp monster.

episodes.title: Hopeless and Changeless
episodes.plot: The guys head to the park asking strangers to agree with their bizarre points of view, then give classless lessons about real estate. Plus, tonight's loser finds himself in a harrowing race to the finish at the racetrack.

episodes.title: Stripped of Dignity
episodes.plot: The guys get a taste of babysitting while asking reluctant strangers to watch their kid, then head to the grocery store to conduct taste(less) tests with shoppers, and the loser is forced to strip for the wrong people.

episodes.title: The Taunted House
episodes.plot: The guys get extra cheesy at a pizza parlor, then head to Wall Street where they ask strangers to help translate bizarre text messages in Spanish. And trapped in a haunted house, a nightmare comes to life for the big loser.

episodes.title: Doomed
episodes.plot: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr take in more than they bargained for while working at a tailor shop, then convince strangers to hand over their cell phones. And the big loser sacrifices his childhood for a punishment three months in the making.
